@p
  Scalafix is a new tool to help Scala 2.x compile with @dotty(),
  a next generation compiler for Scala.
  This effort follows the Scala Center Advisory Board proposal:
  @lnk("Clarification of Scala to Dotty migration path", "http://scala-lang.org/blog/2016/05/30/scala-center-advisory-board.html#the-first-meeting").

@p
  Read the announcement of the 0.1.0 release
  @lnk("here", "http://www.scala-lang.org/blog/2016/10/24/scalafix.html").

@p
  The project is still in early days of development, so there is not much
  to see here yet.
  Currently, work on scalafix happens mostly in
  @lnk("scala.meta", "http://scalameta.org"),
  the metaprogramming toolkit that powers the scalafix @sect.ref{Rewrites}.

@p
  The name "scalafix" is inspired by
  @lnk("gofix", "https://golang.org/cmd/fix/"),
  a similar tool used to migrate go code.

